Tenendam . . . de me heredibus meis et as- signatis in libera alba firma in feodoque et hereditate imperpetuum . . . In cuius rei testimonium huic presenti carte mee manu mea propria sub- scripte sigillum meum proprium est appensum apud Fendowrie vicesimo tertio die mensis Mercii anno Domini millesimo quingentesimo octuagesimo tertio coram his testibus magistro Dugallo Campbell decano Brechinensi Duncano Campbell suo fratre Thoma Laurence et magistro Andrea Elder notario publico . Sic subscribitur, G. Wischart of Drymme elder. In witnes quherof to thir presentis, subscryuit be Mr. Thomas Ramsay my clark of court and George Wricht my clark substitut notaris, my proper seall of office is ap- pendit, at Brechin the tuentie—sext day of Junii, the zeir of Grod forsaid, ane thousand sex hunderetht and fyue zeiris.
